I am a graduate student in the chemistry department at UVa, looking for a volunteering opportunity. In high-school, i was a bike assembler and mechanic for a few years at the Schererville, IN Trek Bicycle store. There i learned how to build all styles of bikes and do most repairs. I can adjust derailleurs and breaks, install parts, true wheels, and I am always up for a mechanical challenge. I also built a bicycle entirely out of broken parts that i still ride today. 

It is difficult to find time in my schedule since i am a graduate student. Typically, i am available some weekdays in the afternoon and some weekends in the morning or afternoon. I would like to know what volunteer shifts are typical or expected, and what skills are most needed. I would love to serve the community in some way at Charlottesville community bikes.
